The article is a supplemental report from President Biden to the Speaker of the House and the President of the Senate regarding the deployment of United States Armed Forces in support of counterterrorism efforts. The report provides an overview of military operations conducted in various regions, including Afghanistan, Iraq, Syria, Yemen, Saudi Arabia, Jordan, Lebanon, Turkey, East Africa, the Lake Chad Basin and Sahel Region, Cuba, the Philippines, Egypt, Kosovo, and North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) countries in Europe. The President states that these operations are carried out in accordance with the War Powers Resolution and other relevant statutes, and that they have been successful in degrading the capabilities of ISIS in Syria and Iraq. The President also emphasizes his authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive to conduct these operations and assures that his administration regularly communicates with congressional leadership and relevant committees regarding these deployments.